metadata.editComments:
The short measure of harp is a great way to add some unevenness without it being too jarring. 
The orchestral percussion is on full display here: Timpani, bass drum, snare drum, and cymbals. In particular, the snare drum line is important in this part to keep the momentum.

The verse highlights the timpani holding down the low end harmony under the violin... Or is it just double bass backed by bass drum? Bar 15 implies the latter.
I had no melody space to include any of the harp ornamentations, unfortunately.
